WEST NILE VIRUS, HUMAN - ISRAEL (03)
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sun 20 Oct 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ha'aretz, Thu 17 Oct 2002 [edited]

According to Health Ministry figures released yesterday, 26 people
were infected with the West Nile virus this year [2002], and 2 of
them died as a result of the disease. Of the people infected, 2 were
not hospitalized at all. Currently 5 patients are currently in stable
condition at various hospitals across the country. During the same
period last year, 36 people were infected with the disease, and 3 of
them died. West Nile virus has been detected this year in Kiryat Gat,
Migdal Ha'emek, Kfar Sava, Hadera, Rishon Letzion, Kiryat Tivon, Or
Yehuda, a moshav near Eilat, and 3 towns in the Negev.
--
